\A1;{\fSFNS Display|b0|i0|c0|p2;This will be a challenge if we can not somehow associate the dimensions with the block.  If the designer uses the same layer for both the block and dimension, then we should try to use proximity to link them together.The other option might be that the designer uses different layers for the block and dimension but we require both to be appended with "-ELC".\P\PFor items on a layer appended by "-ELC", tasks should only be created by incoming blocks.\P\PSee "Adjustments" page for additional details}

\A1;{\fCalibri|b1|i0|c0|p34;Scenario 1:\P\fSFNS Display|b0|i0|c0|p2;The way this might work is after associating the dimensions with the blocks, the field tech is then presented with the two dimension.  Simply by changing these the block will move.}

\A1;{\fCalibri|b1|i0|c0|p34;Scenario 2:\P\fSFNS Display|b0|i0|c0|p2;This scenario is bit more challenging.  The second block is based on the location of the first block.  This may take an additional set of logic.  We would need to identify the first,or base dimension.  Perhaps one that is associated with only one block.  After that we could work across the series.\P\PAlthough these are linked they are still independent tasks.\P\PIf you modify one then is should ask if you want to push the change to the others.}

\A1;\pxi-1,l3,t3;{\fSymbol|b0|i0|c2|p18;^I}{\fCalibri|b0|i0|c0|p34;Dimension change indicated by color change.  Because the task is a copy of the original item then after the move we can see the original.\P{\fSymbol|b0|i0|c2|p18;^I}The two tasks willlikely be an issue.  In previous discussion I had mentioned dimming the old one and/or having an option to hide the previous.  This may be an issue because there may be other electrical dimensions on the plan that were not made into tasks.  I am notsure how hard it would be to differentiate the between them.\P{\fSymbol|b0|i0|c2|p18;^I}Another issue to consider has to do with workflow.  We decided that the system will look for changes in a blocks location, if it recognizes a change it will askif you want to create a task.  In this case we would need to base the compare on the block that we moved, not the one in the previous DXF.}
